Q1: Job Scheduling (Backtracking / NP-Hard Problem)

jobs=[
{"name":"J1","deadline":5,"skill":"Java"},
{"name":"J2","deadline":7,"skill":"Python"},
{"name":"J3","deadline":8,"skill":"Java"}
]
employees={
"E1":["Java"],
"E2":["Python","Java"]
}
assignment={}
def is_valid(job,employee):
    return job["skill"] in employees[employee]
def schedule_jobs(job_index):
    if job_index==len(jobs):
